<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you still don‚Äôt know </span><b>what to see in Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and are worried about not knowing what you‚Äôll find upon arrival, we offer you a basic guide with the most important elements related to this country.¬†It will give you </span><b>a general idea about the wonderful trip that you‚Äôre preparing</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or that you are about to take.</span></p>
<div id="toc_container" class="toc_light_blue no_bullets"><p class="toc_title">Contenido</p><ul class="toc_list"><li><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></li></ul></div>
<h2><span id="Basic_points_to_consider_when_travelling_to_Costa_Rica">Basic points to consider when travelling to Costa Rica</span></h2>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20468" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20468" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tucan-10-min-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Costa Rica </span><b>is a very special country that you will fall in love with from the first moment</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It has some stunning beaches where you can relax and enjoy a unique natural sight. You can explore cloud and rain forests which house an impressive diversity of plants and animals.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">And Costa Rica is a country where nature prevails and where </span><b>you can get to know unique plants and curious animals such</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as toucans, sloths, monkeys, whales, turtles, and caimans, among others. In addition, </span><b>you‚Äôll have the possibility to visit volcanoes</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, hot springs, waterfalls and explore the jungle by zip line.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>It‚Äôs very safe to travel to Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It‚Äôs a country where </span><b>you can travel with family and children</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. You can even rent a car. This is the best option to travel freely to every corner of the country and make good use of your time.</span></p>
<h3><span id="Pass_through_Puntarenas">Pass through Puntarenas</span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20798" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20798" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Puntarenas-townw-min-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For example, you can visit </span><b>Puntarenas</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the largest province in the country. It‚Äôs a city with a lot of history due to its strategic position. It has one of the most important ports in the country and beautiful beaches such as Mal Pa√≠s, Santa Teresa and Boca Barranca, where you can also surf.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">In </span><a href="https://asuaire.com/costarica/destinos/disfruta-deportes-acuaticos-diversion-tropical-la-ciudad-portuaria-puntarenas"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Puntarenas</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> there is also the Carara National Park and the </span><a href="https://www.govisitcostarica.co.cr/region/city.asp?cID=439" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cabo Blanco Natural Reserve.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">Although </span><b>the weather is quite stable</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, it‚Äôs best if you inform yourself about the weather conditions in the regions you visit. The country has </span><b>a wide variety of microclimates</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> which may determine the type of clothing you should pack.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><b>In general there are two seasons</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> : the <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/en/costa-rica-en/why-green-season-costa-rica?lang=en">dry season</a> (marked as the summer season) which is from December to April, and the rainy season (the winter season) that runs from May to November. The months when it rains the most are September and October.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the typical dishes of Costa Rican cuisine is Gallo Pinto, a breakfast made with rice, beans and spices. Another <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/en/costa-rica-en/how-to-make-costa-rican-gallo-pinto">characteristic meal</a> is </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Casado</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, a lunch of rice, beans, meat, salad and vegetables. </span><b>You can try them in the &#8220;sodas&#8221;</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, small restaurants frequented by the &#8220;ticos&#8221; (the locals of Costa Rica).</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21180" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21180" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Gallo-pinto-1-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Although Costa Rica is a country of only 51,100 km¬≤, it </span><b>has about 60 natural parks or protected areas</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, founded during the conversion of the country&#8217;s foreign debt into conservation bonds in the 1980s.</span></p>
<h3><span id="Guanacaste_and_its_natural_parks">Guanacaste and its natural parks</span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19952" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-600x338.jpg 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-900x506.jpg 900w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19952" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-600x338.jpg 600w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Tortuguero-Arenal-Monteverde-y-Guanacaste-900x506.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the </span><b>Guanacaste</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> region you can visit </span><b>the Barra Honda National Park with its impressive limestone caverns</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">; the Rincon de la Vieja Volcano National Park, </span><a href="https://www.visitcostarica.com/es/costa-rica/where-to-go/protected-areas/guanacaste-national-park" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Guanacaste National Park</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and Santa Rosa, Palo Verde National Park, Tenorio Volcano National Park or Las Baulas Marine National Park, among others.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Costa Rica </span><b>alone contains 5% of the biodiversity of the whole planet</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It has approximately 900 species of birds, more than 250 species of mammals and 227 species of reptiles.¬†You‚Äôll be stunned by the beauty of sloths, jaguars, whales, dolphins and toucans.</span></p>
<h3><span id="Enjoy_nature_in_Tortuguero">Enjoy nature in Tortuguero</span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20722" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20722" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-Canals-in-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can‚Äôt miss </span><b>Tortuguero</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, one of the country‚Äôs wildest areas, where you can enjoy one of the most incredible natural phenomena: </span><b>green, hawksbill and leatherback turtles laying eggs</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It‚Äôs located on the <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/en/costa-rica-en/costa-rica-surf-what-you-should-know">Caribbean coast</a>, in the province of Lim√≥n. It‚Äôs a protected natural park where manatees, crocodiles and a great diversity of fish and crustaceans live side-by-side.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20446" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20446" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Tortuguero-05-min-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you haven‚Äôt yet had the opportunity to see a live volcano, Costa Rica is the ideal place to get to know this strange natural phenomena. Within its territory, </span><b>there are about 200 volcanoes</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> because the country is within the Pacific Ring of Fire. One example is the </span><a href="https://abordodelmundo.com/volcan-arenal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Arenal volcano</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which is located within the Arenal Volcano National Park. It‚Äòs one of the most active volcanoes in the region.</span></p>
<h3><span id="The_beautiful_city_of_Liberia">The beautiful city of Liberia</span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20629" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20629" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675" title="" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you want to visit a typical city with good nightlife, don‚Äôt hesitate to spend a few days in </span><b>Liberia</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, in the province of Guanacaste. It‚Äôs a very special city where you‚Äôll find </span><b>very quaint colonial architecture</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, a splendid central park, museums and historical monuments. It has an international airport and is a perfect starting point for going to the regions‚Äô beaches. Be sure to try its </span><b>excellent sugarcane juice</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and typical slushies.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">When <a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/en/costa-rica-en/5-active-volcanoes-in-costa-rica">travelling to Costa Rica</a>, you‚Äôll finally </span><b>understand the meaning of its ‚ÄúPura vida‚Äù motto</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Costa Rica will show you the benefits of an environment where relaxation and the joy of living prevail.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Surely you‚Äôll be looking forward to the flight now that you know what to see in Costa Rica. It will change your life forever!</span></p>
		</div>

